{"toolName":"view","data":{"sessionId":"18730aff-7d46-4ff6-acd0-0d5d7d869469","timestamp":1772357937583,"cwd":"D:\\Repositories\\max-ai-ui\\playground\\backend","toolName":"view","toolArgs":{"path":"D:\\Repositories\\max-ai-ui\\.playground\\workflows\\comedy_club.md"},"toolResult":{"resultType":"success","textResultForLlm":"1. # Agent Workflow & Handoff Protocol\n2. \n3. its a simulation of a comedy show.\n4. \n5. ## How Handoffs Work\n6. \n7. The **Handoff:** format is how you **invoke/call other agents** as subagents or team members to continue the workflow.\n8. \n9. **Format:** `**Handoff:** @agent-name \"message about what you did\"`\n10. \n11. This is an **ACTION** - writing this line will trigger the specified agent to execute the next step.\n12. \n13. ## Agent Handoff Chain\n14. \n15. | From Agent | To Agent | Condition | Handoff Format |\n16. |------------|----------|-----------|----------------|\n17. | **comedian** | heckler | always | `**Handoff:** @heckler \"[message]\"` |\n18. | **heckler** | comedian | if joke rating < 8 out of 10 | `**Handoff:** @comedian \"[message]\"` |\n19. | **heckler** | audience | if joke rating >= 8 out of 10 | `**Handoff:** @audience \"[message]\"` |\n20. | **audience** | comedian | till 10 funny jokes are delivered | `**Handoff:** @comedian \"[message]\"` |\n21. \n22. ## Standard Workflow\n23. \n24. ```\n25. @comedian\n26.   Γåô\n27. @heckler\n28.   Γåô (if joke rating < 8 out of 10)       Γåô (if joke rating >= 8 out of 10)\n29. @comedian (cycle)                      @audience                          \n30.   Γåô\n31.   Γåô (till 10 funny jokes are delivered)\n32. @comedian (cycle back)\n33. ```\n34. "}},"toolArgs":{"path":"D:\\Repositories\\max-ai-ui\\.playground\\workflows\\comedy_club.md"},"terminalId":"7e80e916-26da-4f5f-add2-3dc5300a7c8a","sessionId":"18730aff-7d46-4ff6-acd0-0d5d7d869469","taskId":"aksja-1772357689513","cwd":"D:\\Repositories\\max-ai-ui\\playground\\backend","toolResult":{"resultType":"success","textResu